@NODE Source_Code "Source Code"
The source code is not available. I have not released, and probably will
not release it. Please don't write or call asking for the source code or
the algorithm. Your local library may have helpful books. Or, if you have
access to Internet and CARL, you will find a lot of documentation on
random dot stereograms.
@ENDNODE




@NODE Need_Help "Need Help?"
Sometimes it's easier to see these when they are on paper. If you are
having difficulty seeing these, try printing them out on an 8.5 x 11 page.
It helps some people to have the two dots at the top of the page. After
some practice, you probably won't even need the dots.

If you are stuck, but are still interested, send me a self-addressed,
stamped envelope, and I will send you a couple of my printouts.

If you still need more help, or have suggestions, comments, bug reports,
or anything to say, I can be reached in several ways:

Snail Mail:	Ben Sutter
