@NODE History "History"
version 2.1	Released 14-April-1994
		Screenmode Requester can be used
		Display Beep after operation can be disabled
		Stats can now be in main RDS window
		Window position is saved in prefs files
		All new features are save in prefs file
		I included the correct iff.library version this time!

version 2.0	Released 14-February-1994
		RDS now has a GUI!!!!
		Random dots can be replaced with a custom bitmap
		Custom seed can be used
		Custom focal width can be used
		Decode and encode are now included in one executable
		Preferences can be saved

version 1.1	Released 4-June-1993
		Added some minor optomization
		Included UnRDS, a stereogram decoder
		RDS no longer requires version 18 or better of iff.library

version 1.0	Released 20-May-1993
		Initial Release
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Project_Open "Open Main"
Opens an @{" ASL file requester " Link ASL_FileReq} and attempts to load the selected file

If an non-existant file or bad ILBM file is selected, an appropriate error
message is given.
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Project_Save "Save Main"
Opens an @{" ASL file requester " Link ASL_FileReq} and attempts to save the main picture as the
selected file

If the file already exists, a selector will appear.
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Project_Close "Close Main"
De-allocates the main bitmap. If it has been encoded or decoded but not
saved, a selector will appear.
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Project_Open_BitMap "Open Custom BitMap"
Opens an @{" ASL file requester " Link ASL_FileReq} and attempts to load the selected file

If an non-existant file or bad ILBM file is selected, an appropriate
error message is given.

When a custom bitmap is loaded, it is used to replace the repeating
pattern of random dots. When the custom bitmap is closed, random dots will
be used.

The custom bitmap will be cropped or tiled as necessary to fill the needed
space.
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Project_Close_BitMap "Close Custom BitMap"
When a custom bitmap is loaded, it is used to replace the repeating
pattern of random dots. When the custom bitmap is closed, random dots will
be used.

The custom bitmap will be cropped or tiled as necessary to fill the needed
space.
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Project_Disp_Prefs "Display Using Preferences"
This option will display the main picture or alternate bitmap depending
on which menu was selected, and will open a screenmode requester if that
option is set to on.

See Also: @{" AGA Support    " Link AGA}
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Project_Disp_Default "Display Using Default Screenmode"
This option will display the main picture or alternate bitmap depending
on which menu was selected, and will use the screenmode found in the IFF
ILBM file regardless of the @{" Ask Screenmode " Link Menu_Settings_Ask_Screenmode} setting.

See Also: @{" AGA Support    " Link AGA}
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Project_Disp_Ask "Display Using Screenmode Requester"
This option will display the main picture or alternate bitmap depending
on which menu was selected, and will open a screenmode requester to
determine the screenmode regardless of the @{" Ask Screenmode " Link Menu_Settings_Ask_Screenmode} setting.

See Also: @{" AGA Support    " Link AGA}
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Project_Stats "Stats"
Displays current info about the program and what's loaded
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Project_About "About"
Displays info about the RDS program
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Project_Quit "Quit"
I can't believe you pressed this button! What are you, a dummy?
Just kidding, this option exits the program.

If the main picture has been encoded or decoded but not saved, a selector
will appear.
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Stereogram_Encode "Encode Stereogram"
Encode the current picture

If no custom bitmap is loaded, it uses random dots. Otherwise, the custom
bitmap will be used.
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Stereogram_Decode "Decode Stereogram"
Decodes the current picture

If a normal un-encoded picture is in memory, the results will be complete
garbage.
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Settings_Seed "Set Seed"
Opens a CON: window to set the seed value

Default: uses a clock based seed
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Settings_Width "Set Focal Width"
Opens a CON: window to set the focal width

Default: uses a width of 1/8 the width of the main picture
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Settings_IFF_On "Set IFF Compress On"
Turns IFF compression on when saving
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Settings_IFF_Off "Set IFF Compress Off"
Turns IFF compression off when saving
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Settings_Display_Beep_On "Turn DisplayBeep on"
The Intuition DisplayBeep() function is called after every encode
or decode operation.
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Settings_Display_Beep_Off "Turn DisplayBeep off"
The Intuition DisplayBeep() function won't be called.
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Settings_Stats_Window_On "Turn Stats Window on"
The RDS window will show the stats found in the Stats window, so you
don't have to use the menu item every time you want to look at something.
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Settings_Stats_Window_Off "Turn Stats Window off"
The RDS window is shrunk down to a small size. The stats are still
available from the menus or by RIGHT-AMIGA-?.
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Settings_Ask_Screenmode_On "Ask For Screenmode"
A Screenmode requester will be opened when a display menu item is
selected.
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Settings_Ask_Screenmode_Off "Don't Ask For Screenmode"
A Screenmode requester will not be opened when a display menu item is
selected. The default screenmode from the IFF ILBM file will be used.
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Settings_Load "Load RDS Settings"
Load RDS settings from ENV:RDS.prefs

Settings are loaded from the prefs file and attributes within the program
are changed accordingly.
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Settings_Use "Use RDS Settings"
Saves RDS settings to ENV:RDS.prefs

Settings that are saved in the prefs file include:
	location, size, directories, and patterns of all file requesters
	location of RDS window.
	a custom seed, if selected
	a custom width, if selected
	whether or not to compress IFF files
	whether or not to beep after encodes and decodes
	whether or not to display stats in the RDS window
	whether or not to open a screenmode requester


NOTE: RDS 2.1 will read your 2.0 prefs file and use defaults for the new
      options where appropriate and save a 2.1 prefs file the next time you
      select use or save prefs.


Defaults are hard-coded into the program if no prefs file is found.
@ENDNODE




@NODE Menu_Settings_Save "Save RDS Settings"
Saves RDS settings to ENV:RDS.prefs and ENVARC:RDS.prefs

Settings that are saved in the prefs file include:
	location, size, directories, and patterns of all file requesters
	location of RDS window.
	a custom seed, if selected
	a custom width, if selected
	whether or not to compress IFF files
	whether or not to beep after encodes and decodes
	whether or not to display stats in the RDS window
	whether or not to open a screenmode requester


NOTE: RDS 2.1 will read your 2.0 prefs file and use defaults for the new
      options where appropriate and save a 2.1 prefs file the next time you
      select use or save prefs.


Defaults are hard-coded into the program if no prefs file is found.
@ENDNODE




@NODE ASL_FileReq "ASL Requesters"
I chose to use the ASL file and screenmode requesters for a few reasons.

1) I like it. The ASL requester is very intuitive and easy to use. I don't
   like reqtools because it has a max width for the window and doesn't show
   datestamps for the files. Req.library is just plain out of the question,
   as is arp.library.


2) using the Commodore standard file requester helps to promote ONE
   standard file requester instead of having who knows how many different
   libraries each with its own file requester. If a significant number of
   people don't like it, I may add in a later version an option to select
   what requester to use, but so far, nobody has complained.
@ENDNODE




@NODE AGA "AGA Support"
At this time, I cannot guarantee if any AGA screenmodes will work. Once
AmigaDOS 3.1 is released (if it is EVER released), I can emulate most AGA
screenmodes on my Picasso board, so I can at least test these modes to see
if they work.

I have attempted to support the new 96 bit as opposed to 12 bit palettes
from 3.x and above, if you are running it. Although, ALL I had was the
function prototypes, so I cannot quarantee what will happen in AGA
screenmodes or if the full palettes will be used when viewing a bitmap.

@ENDNODE




